  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis\n\n**Current state: zero tests.** No `test_*.py`, no `pytest.ini`/`pyproject.toml`, no `conftest.py`. The `.claude-flow/logs/headless/testgaps_*` files are stale automation logs, not tests. All ~1,800 lines across 8 modules are unverified by automation.\n\nBelow: gaps by module, ranked by risk, with skeletons. Assumes `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio` + `respx` (for mocking `httpx`).\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — highest value, zero dependencies, pure logic\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `parse_posted_at`: epoch-seconds vs epoch-milliseconds boundary (the `>= 1e12` branch), negative/garbage strings, empty string, non-`Z` ISO with offset, naive ISO (no tz) → should default to UTC.\n- `Job.key` stability across mutated fields (title changes shouldn't change key).\n- `content_hash` stability/sensitivity (title/location/url/department change it; salary/posted_at do NOT — that's a real, non-obvious design choice worth pinning).\n- `to_row()` drops `raw`, includes computed `key`/`content_hash`.\n\n```python\n# test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso_with_trailing_z(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is not None\n\n    def test_iso_naive_defaults_to_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-01T00:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_epoch(self):\n        # boundary: abs(n) check on negative numbers\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"-1000\") is not None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        return Job(**{**base, **kw})\n\n    def test_key_stable_across_title_change(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(title=\"Engineer\"), self._job(title=\"Sr Engineer\")\n        assert j1.key == j2.key\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self):\n        j1, j2 = self._job(title=\"A\"), self._job(title=\"B\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_salary_and_posted_at(self):\n        j1 = self._job(salary_range=\"100k\", posted_at=\"2026-01-01\")\n        j2 = self._job(salary_range=\"200k\", posted_at=\"2026-02-02\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_computed_fields(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] and row[\"content_hash\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — pure logic, currently zero tests\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Word-boundary regex matching (`\\bword\\b`) — e.g. `include=[\"ML\"]` shouldn't match \"HTML\".\n- `exclude` takes precedence over `include` when both match.\n- `locations` is substring/case-insensitive, not word-boundary.\n- `cutoff`: jobs with unparseable `posted_at` are always **kept** (documented intentional behavior — worth pinning down).\n- `filter_jobs` with empty rules dict / missing keys.\n- `max_age_days` as string vs float from YAML.\n\n```python\n# test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    base = dict(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\",\n                url=\"u\", location=\"Remote\", department=\"Eng\")\n    return Job(**{**base, **kw})\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_include_word_boundary_not_substring(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"HTML Developer\"), include=[\"ML\"]) is False\n\n    def test_exclude_takes_precedence_over_include(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Senior ML Manager\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"ML\"], exclude=[\"Manager\"]) is False\n\n    def test_locations_is_case_insensitive_substring(self):\n        assert match(_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"])\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_confirmed_old_posting(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        old = _job(posted_at=(cutoff - timedelta(days=5)).isoformat())\n        assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_date(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=\"garbage\"), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_no_filters_matches_everything(self):\n        assert match(_job()) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_empty_rules_keeps_all(self):\n        jobs = [_job(), _job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_as_string_from_yaml(self):\n        jobs = [_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": \"30\"}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — critical (dedup correctness), needs a real sqlite fixture\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `diff()`: new vs changed vs unchanged classification; `last_seen` bump on unchanged rows.\n- Column migration path (`_migrate`) — simulate a pre-`salary_range` DB.\n- `next_seq` concurrency claim (the docstring explicitly calls out `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` for parallel workers — this is exactly the kind of invariant that needs a regression test, especially given the memory note about parallel worker collisions).\n- `added_since` ordering and strict `>` boundary (not `>=`).\n- Round-trip through `Store` context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__` closes connection).\n\n```python\n# test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport threading\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=f\"https://x/{ext_id}\", **kw)\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_first_seen_job_is_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and not changed\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert not new and not changed\n\n    def test_content_change_reports_as_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n        assert not new and len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_still_bumps_last_seen(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        row1 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        row2 = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n        assert row2[\"last_seen\"] >= row1[\"last_seen\"]\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_migrates_db_missing_salary_range_column(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        s = Store(path)  # must not raise\n        assert \"salary_range\" in {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        s.close()\n\nclass TestNextSeq:\n    def test_increments_sequentially(self, store):\n        assert [store.next_seq(\"k\") for _ in range(3)] == [1, 2, 3]\n\n    def test_concurrent_claims_are_unique(self, tmp_path):\n        # Regression test for the parallel-worker-collision failure mode\n        s = Store(tmp_path / \"concurrent.db\")\n        results = []\n        def claim():\n            results.append(s.next_seq(\"report_seq\"))\n        threads = [threading.Thread(target=claim) for _ in range(10)]\n        [t.start() for t in threads]; [t.join() for t in threads]\n        assert sorted(results) == list(range(1, 11))\n        s.close()\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_excludes_row_at_exact_timestamp(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[\"first_seen\"]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `notify.py` — no tests for env-var gating or failure isolation\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Each notifier is a no-op unless its env vars are set AND there's something to send — every notifier needs a \"gated off\" test and an \"activates\" test.\n- `dispatch()`'s exception isolation: **this is the most important untested behavior** — one notifier raising must not block the others (currently only verifiable by reading the `try/except` in the loop).\n- `notify_sms._sms_body`: ASCII-only truncation at `limit`, the \"+N more\" line.\n- `notify_sms`: `resp.raise_for_status()` propagates HTTP errors from Twilio.\n\n```python\n# test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport notify\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(title=\"Eng\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\")\n\nclass TestDispatchIsolation:\n    def test_one_notifier_failing_does_not_block_others(self, capsys):\n        calls = []\n        def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"smtp down\")\n        def ok(new, changed): calls.append(\"ok\")\n        with patch.object(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [boom, ok]):\n            notify.dispatch([_job()], [])\n        assert calls == [\"ok\"]\n        assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\nclass TestSlack:\n    def test_noop_without_webhook_url(self, monkeypatch, respx_mock=None):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])  # must not raise / must not call httpx\n\n    def test_noop_when_nothing_new_or_changed(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack/x\")\n        notify.notify_slack([], [])  # respx with no registered route would fail if called\n\nclass TestSmsBody:\n    def test_truncates_and_appends_more_count(self):\n        jobs = [_job(title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\n    def test_raises_for_status_on_twilio_error(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"tok\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")\n        # mock httpx.post to return a 400 response; assert HTTPStatusError propagates\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `fetchers.py` — largest file, mostly untested; split into parser tests (pure, cheap) and fetch-loop tests (need `respx`)\n\n**Gaps (parsers — pure functions, highest ROI):**\n- Every `parse_*` function needs at least one \"happy path\" + one \"missing/null field\" test. Highest-risk ones:\n  - `parse_apple`/`_apple_hydration`: hand-rolled JS-string quote scanner (`_apple_hydration`) — needs a test for escaped quotes inside the JSON blob, and a \"marker not found → None\" test.\n  - `_apple_posted_at`: nanosecond-precision timestamp truncation regex — untested boundary (7-char truncation of fractional seconds).\n  - `parse_google`/`_extract_ds1`: two-pattern regex fallback (primary vs `sideChannel`-moved fallback) is untested; malformed JSON → `[]`.\n  - `parse_deshaw`/`parse_twosigma`: regex-based HTML scraping with dedup (`seen` set) — untested for duplicate cards, missing location.\n  - `_amazon_posted_at`: malformed date string → `\"\"` (currently relies on bare `except`).\n  - `_bd_location`: recursive parent-chain walk — untested for `None` chain, circular-safe (it isn't guarded against cycles).\n- `parse_lever`/`_lever_salary`: missing `salaryRange` falls back to `salaryDescriptionPlain`.\n\n**Gaps (network layer — needs `respx`):**\n- `_request`: retry on 429/500/502/503/504, **no retry** on 404/401, exponential backoff timing, exhausted retries raises `RuntimeError`.\n- Pagination loops (`fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_apple`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_workday`, `fetch_bytedance`): stop-on-empty-page, `seen` dedup across pages, `max_pages` cap actually enforced.\n- `fetch_meta`: `for (;;);` JSON prefix stripping, GraphQL `errors` key raising `RuntimeError`.\n- `fetch_all`: a single source's exception doesn't kill the whole batch (`one()`'s try/except); `concurrency` semaphore actually caps in-flight requests; client is closed only when `fetch_all` created it (`owns_client`), not when caller passed one in.\n- `fetch_source`: unknown `ats` raises `ValueError` listing known ATS names.\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_apple,\n                       _apple_posted_at, _apple_hydration, parse_google, _extract_ds1,\n                       _amazon_posted_at, parse_amazon, _bd_location)\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_missing_optional_fields_do_not_crash(self):\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1}]})\n        assert jobs[0].title == \"\" and jobs[0].location == \"\"\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_falls_back_to_plain_description(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"DOE\"}) == \"DOE\"\n\n    def test_formats_range_with_currency(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\nclass TestApplePostedAt:\n    def test_truncates_nanosecond_precision(self):\n        result = _apple_posted_at(\"2026-01-01T00:00:03.812668311Z\")\n        assert result == \"2026-01-01T00:00:03.812668+00:00\"\n\n    def test_empty_input_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _apple_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\nclass TestAppleHydration:\n    def test_marker_not_found_returns_none(self):\n        assert _apple_hydration(\"<html>no marker</html>\") is None\n\n    def test_handles_escaped_quotes_in_js_string(self):\n        html = 'window.__staticRouterHydrationData = JSON.parse(\"{\\\\\"a\\\\\":1}\");'\n        assert _apple_hydration(html) == {\"a\": 1}\n\nclass TestExtractDs1:\n    def test_malformed_json_returns_empty_list(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"key: 'ds:1', data:[not json], sideChannel\") == []\n\n    def test_falls_back_when_sidechannel_missing(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', foo, data:[[1,2]] });\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == [1, 2]\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    def test_valid_date_normalizes_to_iso(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_malformed_date_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\nclass TestBdLocation:\n    def test_none_chain_returns_empty_string(self):\n        assert _bd_location(None) == \"\"\n\n    def test_walks_city_state_country(self):\n        node = {\"en_name\": \"SF\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"CA\", \"parent\": {\"en_name\": \"US\"}}}\n        assert _bd_location(node) == \"SF, CA, US\"\n```\n\n```python\n# test_fetchers_network.py\nimport httpx, pytest, respx\nfrom fetchers import _request, fetch_source, fetch_all, FETCHERS\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRequestRetry:\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self, respx_mock):\n        route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x/test\").mock(\n            side_effect=[httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={})])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x/test\", retries=2)\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n        assert route.call_count == 2\n\n    async def test_no_retry_on_404(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://x/test\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/test\", retries=3)\n        assert respx_mock.calls.call_count == 1\n\n    async def test_exhausted_retries_raises_runtime_error(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://x/test\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x/test\", retries=2)\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_kill_batch(self, respx_mock):\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/bad/jobs\",\n                       params={\"content\": \"false\"}).mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        respx_mock.get(\"https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/good/jobs\",\n                       params={\"content\": \"false\"}).mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"X\"}]}))\n        sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"bad\"},\n                   {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"good\"}]\n        jobs = await fetch_all(sources, concurrency=2)\n        assert len(jobs) == 1\n\n\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises_value_error(self):\n        import httpx as _h\n        async with _h.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `pipeline.py` — integration seam, currently untested end-to-end\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `load_config`: defaults applied when keys missing (`sources`, `filters`, `db`, `concurrency`).\n- `run()` with `dry_run=True`: no `Store` touched, no notifications dispatched, returns `{\"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}` regardless of matches.\n- `run()` full path: fetch → filter → diff → dispatch wiring, using mocked `fetch_all`/`Store`.\n\n```python\n# test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\nclass TestLoadConfig:\n    def test_applies_defaults_for_missing_keys(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n        cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n        assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8 and cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nclass TestRun:\n    async def test_dry_run_never_touches_store_or_notifies(self, tmp_path):\n        cfg_path = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n        cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'x.db'}\\n\")\n        with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as MockStore, \\\n             patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n            result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n        MockStore.assert_not_called()\n        mock_dispatch.assert_not_called()\n        assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` — deterministic helpers untested (the LLM-facing modes are out of scope, but these pure/IO helpers aren't)\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first-run window fallback (no marker), `--posted-days` filtering with undated-kept vs `--dated-only` dropped, group-boundary truncation logic (the `groupby` + `watermark` interaction is subtle — a test should prove a partial group is never truncated mid-group).\n- `cmd_db_mark`: rejects a non-ISO watermark (exit code 2), `--now` vs explicit watermark precedence.\n- `_normalize_ats`: smart quotes/dashes replaced in body text but **not** inside `<style>`/`<script>`/tag attributes — this split-and-rejoin logic is exactly the kind of regex-heavy code that silently breaks on layout changes.\n- `_apple_hydration`-style parsing already covered above; `agent.py`'s own `_chrome_bin` discovery order (env var → PATH → hardcoded app paths) is untested.\n\n```python\n# test_agent.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_replaces_smart_quotes_in_body_text(self):\n        html = \"<p>\\u201cHello\\u201d</p>\"\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert '\"Hello\"' in out and counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_style_block_content(self):\n        html = \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>a\\u2014b</p>\"\n        out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n        assert \"\\u2014\" in out.split(\"</style>\")[0]  # untouched inside style\n        assert \"a-b\" in out  # replaced in body\n\nclass TestDbMark:\n    def test_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(tmp_path / \"missing.yaml\")])\n        # argparse/config load happens before validation in some paths — adjust\n        # to actually reach the ISO check with a valid --config fixture.\n        assert rc == 2\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Missing integration test entirely\n\nNo test exercises `cli.py` → `pipeline.run_sync` → `fetch_all` → `filter_jobs` → `Store.diff` 